    "arXaualog Vol 62 No 38 UHTS Friday 21 September 1962 ANNIVERSARY OBSERVERS Military and civilian artlclantv in the 20th anniversary celebration last Friday of the Naval Supply Depot here listen to one of various guest seakers The observance was held in front of Bldg 11 An anniversary hall Friday night closed oat the festive event Formal Program Gala Ball Highlight NSD Anniversary A formal ceremony and an anniversary ball last Friday high lighted the 20th anniversary of the commissioning of the Naval Supplv Depot here The formal program held from 1530 to 1630 outside of Building 11 featured welcoming remarks by RADM J S Dorsey Naval Base Commander general remarks by CAPT Jack Dan Naval Supply Depot Commanding Officer and greetings and the reading of the proclamation pro claiming Naval Supply Depot Week in Newport by Newport Mayor Charles A Hambly State Senator Joseph A Sav age also addressed the military and civilian dignitaries present at the ceremony Guest speaker for the occasion was RADM John W Crumpacker Chief of the Bureau of Supplies and Accounts Hlstorv Traced RADM Crumpacker traced the history of the development of the supply depot cited its importance GREETINGS and reading of a proclamation proclaiming"
